</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">A distinction among the three methodologies of scientific inquiry: <i>recognising</i> (pertaining to philosophical, theological, and speculative research), <i>explaining</i> (pertaining to mathematical and physical research) and <i>understanding</i> (pertaining to historical research); see: Johann Gustav Droysen, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=7_lrAAAAIAAJ"><i>Grundriss der Historik</i></a>, Verlag von Veit &amp; Comp., 1868, p. 11: §14.</span>
